de.upb.m2m.quality.casestudies.javaemf
Class ShapesRule7

java.lang.Object
  de.upb.m2m.quality.casestudies.javaemf.ShapesRule7

public class ShapesRule7
extends java.lang.Object

This transformation specifies a 1:1 duality relation by transforming circles to arrows and vice versa. In case a circle has no incoming arrows, it is connected to a new, "initial" square. In case a circle has no outgoing arrows, it is connected to a new, "final" square. Furthermore, the transformation assumes that there are only circles and arrows within the source model. Implementation time: 45 Minutes.

Version:
0.1
Author:
Sebastian Lehrig (lehrig@mail.upb.de)
See Also:
Plugin "Rule7" (original scenario)
